": "call_TI3TJVqu9nKGKwT4RepZoMdA|fc_0ec8dbc3fdaeda6d0169f4e787190c8190bd1e2afddd4258d4", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/src/test/java/commons_beanutils/commons_beanutils_core/JDBCDynaClassTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.sql.Time;\nimport java.sql.Types;\n", "newText": "import java.sql.Date;\nimport java.sql.Types;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void introspectsJdbcMetadataColumnClassesThroughPublicResultSetDynaClass() throws Exception {\n        CountingClassLoader countingClassLoader = new CountingClassLoader(JDBCDynaClassTest.class.getClassLoader(),\n                String.class.getName());\n        ClassLoader previousContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(countingClassLoader);\n\n            ResultSetDynaClass dynaClass = new ResultSetDynaClass(createResultSet(), false);\n\n            DynaProperty name = dynaClass.getDynaProperty(\"NAME\");\n            DynaProperty startedAt = dynaClass.getDynaProperty(\"STARTED_AT\");\n            assertThat(dynaClass.getDynaProperties()).hasSize(2);\n            assertThat(name.getType()).isSameAs(String.class);\n            assertThat(startedAt.getType()).isSameAs(Time.class);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousContextClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static ResultSet createResultSet() {\n        ResultSetMetaData metadata = createMetadata();\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void introspectsDateColumnUsingJdbcDateClassLiteral() throws Exception {\n        ResultSetDynaClass dynaClass = new ResultSetDynaClass(createResultSet(\"STARTED_ON\", Types.DATE,\n                Date.class.getName()), false);\n\n        DynaProperty startedOn = dynaClass.getDynaProperty(\"STARTED_ON\");\n\n        assertThat(dynaClass.getDynaProperties()).hasSize(1);\n        assertThat(startedOn.getType()).isSameAs(Date.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void introspectsMetadataColumnClassNameThroughContextClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader previousContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(JDBCDynaClassTest.class.getClassLoader());\n\n            ResultSetDynaClass dynaClass = new ResultSetDynaClass(createResultSet(\"ATTEMPTS\", Types.INTEGER,\n                    Integer.class.getName()), false);\n\n            DynaProperty attempts = dynaClass.getDynaProperty(\"ATTEMPTS\");\n            assertThat(dynaClass.getDynaProperties()).hasSize(1);\n            assertThat(attempts.getType()).isSameAs(Integer.class);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousContextClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static ResultSet createResultSet(String columnName, int columnType, String columnClassName) {\n        ResultSetMetaData metadata = createMetadata(columnName, columnType, columnClassName);\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static ResultSetMetaData createMetadata() {\n", "newText": "    private static ResultSetMetaData createMetadata(String columnName, int columnType, String columnClassName) {\n"}, {"oldText": "            if (\"getColumnCount\".equals(methodName)) {\n                return 2;\n            }\n            if (args == null || args.length == 0 || !(args[0] instanceof Integer)) {\n                return defaultValue(method);\n            }\n            int column = (Integer) args[0];\n            if (\"getColumnName\".equals(methodName)) {\n                return column == 1 ? \"NAME\" : \"STARTED_AT\";\n            }\n            if (\"getColumnType\".equals(methodName)) {\n                return column == 1 ? Types.VARCHAR : Types.TIME;\n            }\n            if (\"getColumnClassName\".equals(methodName)) {\n                return column == 1 ? String.class.getName() : Time.class.getName();\n            }\n", "newText": "            if (\"getColumnCount\".equals(methodName)) {\n                return 1;\n            }\n            if (args == null || args.length == 0 || !(args[0] instanceof Integer)) {\n                return defaultValue(method);\n            }\n            if (\"getColumnName\".equals(methodName)) {\n                return columnName;\n            }\n            if (\"getColumnType\".equals(methodName)) {\n                return columnType;\n            }\n            if (\"getColumnClassName\".equals(methodName)) {\n                return columnClassName;\n            }\n"}, {"oldText": "\n    private static final class CountingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final String countedClassName;\n        private int loadAttempts;\n\n        private CountingClassLoader(ClassLoader parent, String countedClassName) {\n            super(parent);\n            this.countedClassName = countedClassName;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (countedClassName.equals(name)) {\n                loadAttempts++;\n            }\n            return super.loadClass(name);\n        }\n\n        private int loadAttempts() {\n            return loadAttempts;\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": ""}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2534, "output": 2122, "cacheRead": 50688, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55344, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777657719029, "responseId": "resp_0ec8dbc3fdaeda6d0169f4e77799a081908f740d2